net.varkhan.base.containers.list
Class SyncIndexedDoubleList

java.lang.Object
  net.varkhan.base.containers.list.SyncIndexedDoubleList
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Iterable, Container<java.lang.Double>, Indexable, Indexed<java.lang.Double>, IndexedCollection<java.lang.Double>, IndexedContainer<java.lang.Double>, IndexedVisitable<java.lang.Double>, IndexedDoubleList, IndexedList<java.lang.Double>, DoubleIterable, DoubleVisitable, IndexedDoubleCollection, IndexedDoubleContainer, IndexedDoubleVisitable, Visitable<java.lang.Double>
public class SyncIndexedDoubleList
extends java.lang.Object
implements IndexedDoubleList, java.io.Serializable

Provide multithread safety over an unsynchronized IndexedList implementation

This class wraps an unsynchronized IndexedList implementation in a read/write synchronized layer, provided all read operations on the underlying list are state-less (i.e. do not modify any field data in the list).

Individual read or write access to list items is thread safe, and iterators are fail-fast, meaning they will throw a ConcurrentModificationException whenever is detected a modification on the underlying list that is not the result of the iterator's own methods.
